<TEXT>News <NODE id="5" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="18" /> Hires <NODE id="25" />Mark Mastalir<NODE id="38" /> as <NODE id="42" />Vice President of Marketing and Partnerships<NODE id="86" /> PR Newswire | Tuesday, 09 February 2016 01:10 (EST) PALO ALTO, Calif., Feb. 9, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- <NODE id="187" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="200" />, the <NODE id="206" />creators<NODE id="214" /> of <NODE id="218" />Lumo Run<NODE id="226" /> , today announced the addition of <NODE id="261" />Mark Mastalir<NODE id="274" /> to the team as <NODE id="290" />Vice President of Marketing and Partnerships<NODE id="334" />. Mark will lead the <NODE id="355" />company<NODE id="362" />'s marketing efforts for the general availability launch of <NODE id="422" />Lumo Run<NODE id="430" />, a sensor technology that coaches you to run more efficiently, improving your performance and reducing the risk of injury. Mark brings to the team a wealth of experience and knowledge in both competitive running and international sports marketing. Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20160208/330985LOGO Prior to joining <NODE id="757" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="770" />, <NODE id="772" />Mark<NODE id="776" /> worked for <NODE id="788" />Hoka One One<NODE id="800" />, a <NODE id="804" />division<NODE id="812" /> of <NODE id="816" />Deckers Outdoor Corporation<NODE id="843" />, as <NODE id="848" />Vice President of Marketing<NODE id="875" />. Under Mark's leadership, <NODE id="902" />Hoka<NODE id="906" />'s sales increased 300 percent in the last year, making <NODE id="962" />HOKA<NODE id="966" /> the fastest growing running shoe brand of all time. Mark has also held global leadership positions at <NODE id="1069" />Reebok<NODE id="1075" />, <NODE id="1077" />NIKE<NODE id="1081" />, the <NODE id="1087" />NBA<NODE id="1090" /> and <NODE id="1095" />Wrigley<NODE id="1102" />. In addition to his accomplished background in sports marketing, Mark is also passionate about running. He began competitively running in 1982 and was an All-American at Stanford in the 1500 meters in 1992. He also competed in the 1992 Olympic Trials in the 1500 meters. We're excited to expand the <NODE id="1402" />Lumo<NODE id="1406" /> <NODE id="1407" />platform<NODE id="1415" /> to help people be the best runners they can be, said <NODE id="1469" />Monisha Perkash<NODE id="1484" />, <NODE id="1486" />CEO<NODE id="1489" /> and co-founder of <NODE id="1508" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="1521" />. As both a competitive runner and experienced global sports marketer, Mark will be key in helping us to launch <NODE id="1633" />Lumo<NODE id="1637" /> <NODE id="1638" />Run<NODE id="1641" /> and access the multi-billion dollar running and wearables market. <NODE id="1708" />Lumo<NODE id="1712" /> <NODE id="1713" />Run<NODE id="1716" />, launched for pre-sale in October 2015, incorporates the personal attention of a running coach with the professional data of a lab. It measures running biomechanics like cadence, bounce and pelvic stability to guide your running form, improving your overall efficiency and performance. <NODE id="2003" />Lumo<NODE id="2007" /> <NODE id="2008" />Run<NODE id="2011" /> is currently available for pre-order online and is expected to ship spring 2016. Monisha and the team have created a product that allows runners and coaches to easily understand and interpret metrics that improve performance, and there is nothing in the market that provides as much useful information to the runner as <NODE id="2331" />Lumo<NODE id="2335" /> <NODE id="2336" />Run<NODE id="2339" />, said Mastalir. As someone who loves to run and compete, I'm proud to be a part of a team pushing the boundaries of the sport. About <NODE id="2473" />Lumo<NODE id="2477" /> <NODE id="2478" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="2491" /> has developed a technology platform that leverages smart sensors and software to optimize performance and address human biomechanics through the real-time tracking of body movement. <NODE id="2674" />Lumo<NODE id="2678" />'s products empower you to be the best version of yourself. Current <NODE id="2746" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="2759" /> products include the <NODE id="2781" />Lumo Lift<NODE id="2790" /> and <NODE id="2795" />Lumo Back<NODE id="2804" /> posture coaches and activity trackers, as well as the <NODE id="2859" />Lumo Run<NODE id="2867" /> smart running shorts. <NODE id="2890" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="2903" /> is privately-held and <NODE id="2926" />headquartered<NODE id="2939" /> in <NODE id="2943" />Palo Alto, CA<NODE id="2956" />.Â  Information on <NODE id="2974" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="2987" /> and their products is available at <NODE id="3023" />www.lumobodytech.com<NODE id="3043" /> Contacts <NODE id="3053" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="3066" /> Tansy Brook +1 (650) 646-2216 media@lumobodytech.com To view the original version on PR Newswire, visit: http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/lumo-bodytech-hires-mark-mastalir-as-vice-president-of-marketing-and-partnerships-300217061.html SOURCE <NODE id="3316" />Lumo Bodytech<NODE id="3329" /> DISCLOSURE: The views and opinions expressed in this article are those of the authors, and do not represent the views of equities.com . Readers should not consider statements made by the author as formal recommendations and should consult their financial advisor before making any investment decisions. To read our full disclosure, please go to: http://www.equities.com/disclaimer You have to be logged in to leave a comment.
